30|$|In {{order to}} support the access of these <b>logical</b> <b>partitions,</b> which are in turn based on the {{granularity}} of the PPUs being scaled, different mappings of these <b>logical</b> <b>partitions</b> into a varying number of physical block-ram banks must be implemented. The number of block-ram banks required for this logical to physical translation of search window data is determined by ⌈(15 +n)/n⌉ [35].|$|R
50|$|Windows must be {{installed}} into a primary partition (and in older systems {{this must be}} the first partition). Linux can {{be installed}} into a partition in any position on the hard drive and can also be installed into <b>logical</b> <b>partitions</b> (within the extended partition). If Linux is installed into a <b>logical</b> <b>partition</b> within the extended partition, it is unaffected by changes in the primary partitions.|$|R
