50|$|Dynamic <b>Logical</b> <b>Partitioning</b> (DLPAR), is the {{capability}} of a logical partition (LPAR) to be reconfigured dynamically, without having {{to shut down the}} operating system that runs in the LPAR. DLPAR enables memory, CPU capacity, and I/O interfaces to be moved nondisruptively between LPARs within the same server.|$|E
